   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/adriennelacour/Comeaux_Louis_T1080.abs.pdf">The interview records recollections of Comeaux's childhood as the son of a cane
            farmer. He recalls his work in an Avery Island salt mine; farming as a sharecropper; the
            routine of sugarcane planting and harvest; cane syrup production; farm labor; early
            transportation; traditional Cajun foods including couche-couche and cracklins; the
            boucherie; and social conditions in Four Corners.</abstract>
